      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This edition is based on <ref target="bibl:Sarma1993">Sarma and Varaprasada Rao 1993</ref>, with my own (AO’s) corrections based on their photograph.</p>
	<p>Varaprasada Rao understood the donor to be a merchant named Āpakuṭi, but generally the personal names of merchants follow the word <foreign xml:lang="mi-Latn">vāṇiya</foreign>, and the word <foreign xml:lang="mi-Latn">āpakuṭi</foreign> suggests, to me, a drinking station rather than a personal name. But much remains unclear.</p>
      </div>
